# BEEDEFI environment configuration.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` when needed. Never commit `.env.local`.
#
# Everything here is optional — without these set, the app falls back to
# deterministic stubs for AI generations and mocked reads for external data.
# That's how it ships in dev today; setting these flips real calls on.

# ---- AI (Phase 6) ---------------------------------------------------------
# OpenRouter — free-tier models rotate; see https://openrouter.ai/models
# Without this set, /studio generations return stubbed responses and the
# header shows a "Stub" indicator.
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# Used by OpenRouter for free-tier prioritization (HTTP-Referer header).
# Defaults to http://localhost:3000.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://beedefi.example

# ---- Data sources (Phase 6) ----------------------------------------------
# BeeCodeFi learning data — wire when NeonDB migration on BeeCodeFi is done.
# DATABASE_URL=
# Single-user app: identifies the BEEDEFI user inside BeeCodeFi's schema.
# BEECODEFI_USER_ID=akumar@payliance.com

# ---- Optional persistence (Phase 6) --------------------------------------
# Supabase is mentioned in CLAUDE.md as an option; NeonDB is the user's pick.
# Leave these blank unless you wire Supabase auth instead.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
